- **Applicable Scenarios**: Family亲子 hiking, rainy day sightseeing in scenic areas.

### Summary of Key Points for Choosing Anti-Slip Hiking Shoes During Southern Rainy Season
1. Prefer rubber such as **Vibram Megagrip/Contagrip MA/Omni-Grip** (high wet adhesion);
2. Patterns should include **deep teeth ≥6mm + drainage grooves (interlaced/spiral)**;
3. Waterproof shoe soles (GTX or equivalent membrane) are essential to avoid foot moisture leading to instability;  
4. Midsoles with side flip resistance (TPU/composite structure) are suitable for muddy paths with many turns.

For the core needs of users weighing 90kg and above, such as "strong support" and "no toeing out during downhill," the following top 10 hiking boots/shoes are selected based on three key points: **midsole stability structure (anti-twisting, anti-unloading), toe room design (toe protection), rearfoot strong locking (reducing foot forward sliding)**. These cover different scenarios including heavy-duty and light-duty, wide-footed and warm-weather needs:

### TOP1  Scarpa Zodiac Plus GTX Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: Italian benchmark for heavy-duty boots, midsole embedded full-arch TPU stabilizer + high-density EVA cushioning layer, fully anti-twisting, ankle design with 3D立体wrap to prevent side flips due to large weight;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Optimized wide shoe size + toe protection space (15% larger than standard), integrated tongue + Quick Lace quick lacing system locking the rearfoot, preventing foot forward sliding during downhill;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: High-difficulty heavy-duty hiking, complex rocky terrain, GTX waterproof suitable for various weather conditions.

### TOP2  La Sportiva Trango Tech GTX Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: FriXion XT professional mountaineering outsole + midsole TPU skeletal structure supporting up to 100kg+ weight, ankle reinforcement prevents sprain;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Built-in elastic space in toe protection area for downhill movement, wide shoe size design accommodates large-weight feet, rearfoot memory foam wrapping reduces sliding;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: Alpine-style hiking, mixed snow and ice terrain, dual pull on grip and support.

### TOP3  Salomon X Ultra 4 Mid GTX Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: Contagrip MAXX gripping outsole + EnergyCell + cushioning layer + chassis stabilizer for balanced cushioning and anti-unloading, midfoot design supports ankle;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Optimized toe room system for downhill foot movement displacement, Quicklace quick lacing locking the rearfoot instantly to prevent toeing out;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: Light-to-medium-duty heavy-duty hiking, urban off-road terrain, balanced price and professionalism.

### TOP4  Arc'teryx Bora Mid 2 GTX Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: Gathers advanced technology from the Arcteryx brand, Nitrile Rubber non-slip outsole + full arch TPU stabilizer tested for 100kg+ weight, no unloading sensation;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Human-engineered shoe size design + integrated waterproof tongue, rearfoot "locking" system prevents foot sliding, toe protection area with 2cm extra space;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: High-end heavy-duty hiking, high-altitude downhill, balanced waterproofing and support for luxury-level selection.

### TOP5  Hoka One One Kaha 2 GTX Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: Meta-Rocker rolling balance technology + midsole TPU stabilizer, cushioning layer thickness of 20mm without unloading sensation, supports large weight without deformation;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Rolling shoe shape reduces downhill foot forward force, wide toe protection design accommodates large-weight feet, rearfoot locking system prevents sliding;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: Long-distance light-duty hiking, knee discomforters during downhill (rolling technology reduces pressure).

### TOP6  Merrell Moab 3 Mid GTX Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: Air Cushion heel cushioning + Shank stabilizer for supporting up to 90kg+ weight in daily heavy-duty use, midfoot design protects ankle;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Toe protection area with 1.5cm extra space, wide shoe size accommodates large-weight feet, rearfoot wrapping system prevents sliding;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: Entry-level heavy-duty hiking, urban off-road terrain, high-value classic model.

### TOP7  Keen Targhee III Mid WP Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: EVA cushioning + TPU stabilizer for midfoot reinforcement, wide shoe size (20% wider than standard) accommodates large-weight feet, rearfoot locking system prevents sliding;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Toe protection area with "wide buffer zone" design solves toeing out problem, rearfoot locking system prevents foot from sliding even during sudden braking;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: Wide-footed and heavy-weight users, complex terrain downhill, GTX waterproof suitable for various weather conditions.

### TOP8  The North Face Hedgehog Fastpack III Mid GTX Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: Vibram non-slip outsole + TPU stabilizer, midsole TechLite + cushioning layer supporting up to 90kg+ weight without collapse, midfoot design enhances ankle stability;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Toe protection area with "movement buffer zone" for downhill foot movement displacement, rearfoot quick lacing system prevents sliding;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: Light-to-medium hiking, suburban off-road terrain, affordable high-quality option from The North Face.

### TOP9  Columbia Bugaboot Plus IV Omni-Heat Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: Omni-Grip non-slip outsole + midsole TechLite + cushioning layer + stabilizer for balanced warmth and anti-unloading, suitable for cold weather heavy-duty hiking;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Wide toe protection design accommodates large-weight feet, rearfoot memory foam wrapping prevents foot from contracting due to cold causing toeing out;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: Winter snow and ice downhill, cold-heavy duty hiking, preferred choice for users with dual needs of warmth and support.

### TOP10  Timberland PRO Direct Attach 6-inch Steel Toe Hiking Boot
- **Strong Support Core**: Anti-Fatigue cushioning technology + steel toe integrated stabilizer for supporting up to 90kg+ weight in workwear or hiking, Direct Attach process enhances durability;
- **No Toe Out During Downhill**: Steel toe area with elastic space design accommodates large-weight feet, wide shoe size design prevents sliding, rearfoot locking system prevents foot from sliding even during sudden braking;
- **Adaptable Scenarios**: Workwear and light-to-medium-duty hiking, steel toe for added protection.

### Additional Shoe Selection Tips for Heavy-Weight Users
1. **Try-On Key Points**: Toe out often happens due to insufficient toe room; try on with thick socks, lean forward to simulate downhill posture, check if the toe area presses;
2. **Shoe Size Choice**: Large-weight users have feet that tend to expand, prioritize "wide shoe size" (W model);
3. **Stabilizer Priority**: Prioritize full-arch TPU stabilizers over localized ones for stronger anti-twisting capability.

